          <h2 style="             
              font-size: 24px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">BP faces activist pressure as Elliot builds stake</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.longandshort.com/email/images/bp-faces-activist-pressure-as-elliot-builds-stake.png" alt="An image of the BP fuel station" href="https://www.longandshort.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">An image of the BP fuel station. Credits: Bloomberg </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Activist investor Elliot Investment Management has accumulated a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-10-02-2025-h1-1-significant-stake" target="_blank">significant stake</a> in British energy giant BP. This has put significant pressure on the firm, as Elliot is known for pushing corporate shakeups. The investment firm is reportedly aiming for major changes at BP to unlock value. </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">BP has continued to underperform its peers in recent years. The company’s stock is down around 8% over the past five years. This is in stark contrast to energy firms like Shell and Total Energies, which have posted strong shareholder returns. The company started <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-10-02-2025-h1-2-pivoting-away-from-oil" target="_blank">pivoting away from oil</a> in 2020 and moved toward renewable energy.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
