              line-height: 1.2; 
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Super Bowl betting surge gives a boost to struggling gambling stocks</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;">The Super Bowl is set to generate about $1.4 billion in <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-10-02-2025-h2-3-legal-bets" target="_blank">legal bets</a>. This has given a boost to gambling stocks that have struggled for many years. The National Football League’s championship game is set to drive high engagement on betting apps. Shares of major gambling companies have fallen off from peak highs of 2021.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; filter: blur(5px);">DraftKings has fallen about 41%, and MGM Resorts is down 32% from its peak price in 2021. The industry has continued to face regulatory challenges, including increased state taxes. The proposed <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-10-02-2025-h2-4-safe-bet-act" target="_blank">SAFE Bet Act</a> could increase the restriction on gambling companies, posing a challenge to growth.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
